    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop your <strong>potato[es]</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Cut your <strong>broccoli</strong> into small florets</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/salmon-with-pesto-drizzle-goats-cheese-and-roasted-veg/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes </strong>and <strong>broccoli florets </strong>to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until the potatoes are tender and the broccoli is charred, turning once half way \u2013 this is your <strong>roasted veg</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/salmon-with-pesto-drizzle-goats-cheese-and-roasted-veg/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large dry pan over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>pumpkin seeds</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and lightly golden</p><p>Once golden, set aside on a plate (save the pan!)</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/salmon-with-pesto-drizzle-goats-cheese-and-roasted-veg/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Trim, then slice your<strong> spring onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/salmon-with-pesto-drizzle-goats-cheese-and-roasted-veg/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>traditional Italian pesto </strong>in a small bowl with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a splash of <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>pesto dressing</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/salmon-with-pesto-drizzle-goats-cheese-and-roasted-veg/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the vegetables have had about 15 min, return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/salmon-with-pesto-drizzle-goats-cheese-and-roasted-veg/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add the <strong>salmon fillet[s] </strong>(skin-side down), season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>and cook for 8-9 min, turning once halfway, or until cooked through \u2013 this is your<strong> pan-fried salmon</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/salmon-with-pesto-drizzle-goats-cheese-and-roasted-veg/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>pan-fried salmon</strong> over the <strong>roasted vegetables</strong></p><p>Crumble your <strong>goats' cheese </strong>all over, garnish with the <strong>toasted pumpkin seeds </strong>and <strong>chopped spring onions</strong></p><p>Drizzle the <strong>pesto dressing </strong>all over and finish with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
